Docs.summary: Represents a scalar property of an entity type.

remarks.para: This interface is used during model creation and allows the metadata to be modified. Once the model is built, represents a read-only view of the same metadata.
See Modeling entity types and relationships for more information and examples.

summary.para: Gets a value indicating whether or not this property can be modified after the entity is saved to the database.
If , then an exception will be thrown if a new value is assigned to this property after the entity exists in the database.
If , then any modification to the property value of an entity that already exists in the database will be ignored.

Docs.summary: Gets or sets a value indicating whether this property is used as a concurrency token. When a property is configured as a concurrency token the value in the database will be checked when an instance of this entity type is updated or deleted during to ensure it has not changed since the instance was retrieved from the database. If it has changed, an exception will be thrown and the changes will not be applied to the database.
